results.name: Number of complete tree-partitions of a multiset whose multiplicities are the prime indices of n.
comment: This multiset is generally not the same as the multiset of prime indices of n. For example, the prime indices of 12 are {1,1,2}, while a multiset whose multiplicities are {1,1,2} is {1,1,2,3}.

A tree-partition of m is either m itself or a sequence of tree-partitions, one of each part of a multiset partition of m with at least two parts. A tree-partition is complete if the leaves are all multisets of length 1.
example: The a(12) = 17 complete tree-partitions of {1,1,2,3} with the leaves (x) replaced with just x:
